What you need to know:   An estimated Sh55 billion is at the centre of various inheritance disputes in Nakuru by relatives of prominent multi-millionaires, who left behind successful business empires.The families’ billions are now locked in the court battles.The list includes Nakuru politicians Kihika Kimani and Philip Kamau, controversial Naivasha tycoon Gabriel Njoroge popularly known as Fai Amario.